Ours is business family and I am assisting in the management part. 
I possess ORDINARY looks.God has blessed me with versatile talents in the fields of Singing, Music, Writing, Interpretation, Evangelism, Preaching, Teaching, Counselling, Free-lancing etc. 
God healed me thru Music-Ministry and later blessed me with musical talents. I have composed lyrics and music for many Christian Songs.
I feel that all of us should use all the God-Given Talents n Gifts for the Glory of God. Otherwise we will be held accountable for the same one day. 
I am in search for a Qualified Girl who is equally or more talented because I am very particular that MY BETTER HALF SHOULD BE A PERSON WHO ADDS MUSIC n MELODY TO MY LIFE and OTHERS also.  
As an interpreter, God has used me with many frontline Preachers, Evangelists n Speakers. Once I got the privilege to serve as an interpreter to His Excellency Dr APJ Abdul Kalam The President of India. 
If you too are desirous of serving the Lord with all your being and touch many lives with the love of the Lord then feel free to contact me. Please come up with your queries and I request you not to jump into wild conclusions. God bless you as you prayerfully explore this proposal.,"My partner should be a talented girl with versatile talents especially in the fields of music, public speaking and leadership. She should be a devout Christian who understands the importance of touching many lives with the love of Christ. She should have the heart to love the unlovable and should be ready to serve the Lord along with her Career. She should be a compassionate person who cares to serve the downtrodden and the needy. She needs to understand that all the talents which she possesses comes from the Lord and it is imperative to use all God-given talents for the Glory of God and that we will be held accountable if we don't do so. She should be willing to pursue the will of God and do all what pleases him. She should be good at cooking too. I assume that she should have the traits of a true Christian women in word and deed.","My father belonged to the POOVANMALA VILAYIL HOUSE in  THUMPAMON (NORTH) near Elavumthitta. He went to be with the Lord in the year 1992 while praying a closing prayer in the Sunday Service. My mom belongs to the Panampally family lineage from Kulanada. My paternal Granma was from KALAYIL FAMILY.
Our family is involved in the business of tyre remoulding and retreading in Chhattisgarh state (formerly in Madhya Pradesh). Our business is doing very well by the grace of God.
I have 3 Brothers n a Sister. I am the second in the family. I have an elder brother who is married from KUNNATHU Family. He is blessed with a Son.
Next to me is my sister who is a Central Govt Employee. The other two brothers are also involved in our family business.

column1: I'm looking for my long term lover that will cause my heart to skip, leap, and warm at the sight of her. I enjoy making you happy, and have been accused of being a people pleaser, which I don't think is as bad as those that have said that think it is. I have learned that some view arguing as a "love language" itself, not in a mean-spirited way...just to let you know I care enough to argue a point with you. So...I can be taught. I enjoy staying fit and finding new ways to exercise. Although I may appear thin, my shoulders are more than adequate for a safe resting place. Hey...maybe I'll post a shirtless pic...I've heard that's a real plus on this site (how do you enable the sarcasm font again?) All of that to say, I do take care of myself physically and would appteciate that in a partner as well. However, if you want me to train for a marathon or 100 mile bike ride with you, you will have to be patient and let me work up to it as long distance torture is not my first choice. column1: Leaving out details that are already there, let me say that i am born into an iyer (tamilian brahmin) family with liberal values. the only brahminical hang-up i entertain is being vegetarian. i do not smoke or drink. i believe that the institution of marriage is made for two sensible, intelligent and thinking adults who have decided to live together for life, respecting each other's feelings and vow complete faithfulness. i would only respond to girls/ladies who feel comfortable enough to respond directly to me. hey, after all, we re adults arent we? Those that are coy or shy, may pl. ask their parents/relatives to contact my parents (i ll forward your msg. to them). column1: I am coming from respected Rajput family of Bihar. But I lived in the state of Orissa for many years and graduated in Law from Utkal university. During my stay at Orissa I was running a small factory.I am down to earth and very sociable person . I got married to an NRI in early nineties and my marriage lasted for only for six months. Due to this marriage I moved to UK London. After six months I went back to India and again back to UK in 2002 and since then I am in UK. I started my career with giant super stores Tesco in Cambridge and then I worked in various high street stores of UK. In 2006 I joined the British police force and then I moved from Cambridge to Liverpool to work for Mersey side police force as a probation officer. Then I left the police force in 2009 and moved to private sector company. At present I am working for a designer womens garments multinational company based in Liverpool as Head of Security. I am very positive towards my life. I have achieved everything in my life because of my determination and my hard work and I believe in destiny.I am very honest and straightforward in my dealings and I can go to any extent to help out people in difficulty. I am very much concerned about my rights and others rights and I can go to any extent to get justice done. I love children and elderly people and I am always respectful towards them. I am a bit romantic as well. I feel without romance there is no point of your spending your life with someone. I feel it is important in a relationship to understand each others feelings and it is only possible when you truly love someone.In 2005 I became a British citizen. Contact only if you are willing to relocate to UK .If you have any questions about me just let me know and I will be happy to provide you with the answers.,I am looking for nice and beautiful affectionate girl with good academic background and who understand the family value.willing to relocate and loves kids .I would like to be friend first and then it is up to her if she would like to go for relationship. ,My brother and sisters are married and well settled in India . column1: I am a self-made person who has finally found his feet in this crazy but lovable city. Have remained single this long because I wanted to have myself firmly secure and also because I never found the right person. Am financially very sound, no encumbrances whatsoever. Am a Class-I Officer in the Government of India. Am an individual that hates negativity. My priority in life is my family (which obviously would later include the wife and kids) and I would never sacrifice the well-being of my near and dear ones for career or money. Speak the truth as much as possible, think straight and go for the jugular if needled. Have no vices (except being something of a control freak). Enjoy the good things in life, am vegetarian, a teetotaller and a non-smoker. I would like to qualify myself (objectively!!!) as articulate, well-mannered/groomed, modern in outlook (does not mean partying all saturday nights!!!), hailing from a very cosmopolitan background. believe in fair-play and complete commitment and faith in marriage. Love good music, films and books. Enjoy travelling for pleasure (I travel for work, but then that's WORK!). Speak five languages with equal fluency. That's enough of autobiography I guess!!,"Ideals are in the realm of imagination. So, the person who'll make a good wife to me (trust me, I'll make a sincere effort to try and match up to her expectations of being a good husband) is someone with a 9 to 5 job (when I say 9 to 5, I mean it!), who works to keep her mental faculties working and her purse full and not someone who is obsessed with work. Would expect, besides the usual jazz of - decent looking, family values etc., the girl to be a delhi/ncr based (or at least willing to settle in Delhi) VEGETARIAN (Sorry, I can't stand the other smells!), a teetotaller, a non-smoker and NOT a party-pooper. Ideal professions besides 9 to 5 would be teaching or own business. Basically, something that gives her time for herself and then for me because marriage to me means togetherness. Should be willing to co-exist with my parents who are more likely to be great friends of her and be very supportive than be a pain!!!",,,10 Jun 1967,13:36:00,India,Chennai,Athletic,Doesn't Matter,,Brahmin,Brahmin,,,Very Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Self,MA (Arts),"46 yrs, 5ft 11in,

My idea of living life is very simple with a positive outlook towards life. My family is my priority and I never disrespect them. I love to spend most of my time with my family and want to make them feel proud of me. 
Professionally I am a businessman and it requires a lot of time and dedication. I do my work with full authenticity and do fair deals. This is why I have maintained cordial relations with my business associates. My aim in life is to take my business to the height of success. 
My mother is a housewife and father is retired from his profession. I have a brother who is currently engrossed in the advertising business and a sister who is happily married. Further, my family includes my beautiful daughter studying in 12th grade, two sons, one of them is in 10th grade and the other one is in 6th grade. 
In my school education I have completed Intermediate from Kalkaji Government School. I have few friends in my life. I have three children and they are my real support and they are further cooperative in nature.,"I am looking for a non working life partner who is well settled. She should be from a good family and must consider my family as her own and accept my children as her own.

She should be simple in nature so that both of us gel with each other well. Further, she should be flexible and adjustable to fit in to my family. This will help both of us to lead a happy life ahead. One of the major features that I am looking for in my life partner is that she should give due respect to my family and the elder members of my family.

I will give her the freedom to help in my business if she wants. This will make her feel independent and she will also gain confidence. I am ready to help my life partner in every sphere of life whether it is related to home or outside the home. I will be always there for her and always take care of her needs and aspirations.
I assure her about the happy and prosperous future ahead if she is like the one I am looking for.

Well, I am pretty easy to get along with. I gel and get along with most people. I am pretty much confident and can hold the attention of people as well as a good conversation. I like having fun, not at the cost of others though. I am quite religious and believe every person is here for a purpose. And for that he has been gifted the necessary strength and qualities. I discovered this only recently, pretty late in life. Live and let live. I do not judge - for good or bad, since it immediately elevates or demotes the other person or you thereby creating an invisible barrier between you and the other person. I also balance the modern values and traditional thinking reasonably well. At the risk of sounding immodest, I will also say that I am a perfect gentleman, and know how to treat a lady right. Oh, I almost forgot, I have an impeccable character. I like watching movies (English - action, martial arts or new Hindi), listening to music.... I like Hindi pop, Hindi movie songs, Hindi pop, English pop, Soft Rock, Instrumental - English and Hindi general and classical. Yanni is a favorite. Reading is another good past time... especially John Grisham courtroom Dramas, self-improvement books (like 7 habits of highly effective people, etc.) management books, etc. I used to be very active in martial arts earlier and now work out at the gym or go for a walk or run. While I am not much into sports, I do enjoy watching Cricket and Formula racing on TV. I am very much interested in science, following business developments. I am a big foodie and love all kinds of vegetarian or eggetarian foods. I love singing and am a good singer. Non professional, though. AND, I am a fan?tastic joke teller :) I am pretty much an emotional person... can't and don't want to hide my true emotions. I hate liars and manipulators. I guess I am looking for the kind of love one would see in movies ? the romantic dreamer in me?.:). The lady, who is destined to be my partner, will find out after marriage that she will besides being my wife, will always remain my best friend and girlfriend also (keeping the romance alive forever). After certain events in my life, I have learnt to become unstoppable i.e. if I set out to do something, I follow that doggedly, relentlessly, and do not let up till it is done and achieved. I give it more than 100.,"I am looking for a partner who can be not just a wife but also a friend and, well, a soul mate. She should have a sensible head, ambitious, not afraid of challenges in life and take them head on. She should be a homemaker. If she has or wants a career also, that is not an issue. She should be able to tell me straight if she thinks I am wrong. She should have a good family background - no I do not mean money, but reputed family. She should have elegance, charm, poise, and be able to dress, make up, conduct and carry herself well. An attitude is also appealing, though it can misfire also. She should be able to hold an intelligent conversation, and if required and wishes join me in work in office. I must admit I am somewhat inclined towards good looks and a flawless fair complexion. I suppose I am looking for the perfect beauty with brains. Go ahead, call me an MCP if you will, but I am simply being myself and factual instead of hiding behind a mask. Most importantly, she should be able to love my daughter. Without this, all other qualities have no meaning",,,10 Jun 1967,,India,,,,,Marwari,,,,,,Self,B.Com (Commerce),"46 yrs, 5ft 4in,

he is a very kindhearted and honest person.always ready to fulfill his responsibilities.he extremely hates cheating and fraud.very emotional.likes doing poetry and enjoys cooking. he loves exploring the nature and religious places and also remote areas.he likes reading and as far as i believe , he is a spiritual person as well.
our father was self employed but has retired.mother is a house wife. younger sister married and her husband is also self employed.
i am married and have two children. my wife is a house wife. we live in a joint family but he is induldged in touring job so is generally out of station usually in uttaranchal. he is establishing a new business and is thinking of constructing a new house there.,"he seeks a woman who is understanding , caring , loving.
needs a woman who is mature enough to adjust in all situations.
she should be working also.",,,18 Jul 1967,,India,Rest of Uttaranchal,Average,Slim,,Brahmin - Garhwali,,Delhi,,Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Brother,B.Com (Commerce),"46 yrs, 5ft 5in,
